sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1361000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Curli Fiber generator under Pbad induction with positive regulation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We assembled this part in order to examine the concept that change of cell motility by control of CheZ chemotaxis regulator could disturb pre-expressed curli fiber structure. If the inducer occurs, in this case_acacia, CsgB protein will secrete into extracellular and act as nucleator to recruit soluble CsgA monomer into amyloid fibres, and the transcription of CheZ will be downgrade via cI-Plamda NOT gate. If induction condition disappears at a certain point, suppression of CheZ will be discharged. As the result, cells will be more moveable thus disturb or inhibit the establishment of curli structure. And in our final device, the modified CsgA that has ability to absorb nanogold, thus the dynamic detection could achieve by monitoring current change between two electrodes in the culture.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shoujie Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: CsgAC,CsgB collected by PCR from genome of E coli DH5alpha respectively. Other genes are collected from Biobricks Attribution Kit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The PstI loci within CsgA sequence has been replaced from CTGCAG to CTGCCG. And for nano gold absorbability, 6xLinker+2xCys(GGCAGCGGTGGCAGCGGTGGCGGT TGTTGC) and LPFFD(CTGCCGTTCTTTGAT) were added at the C-treminal of CsgA protein respectively. CsgA with7xhis tag at C-treminal were also used for Au-NTA-Ni absorbing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1361998
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Curli Fiber assembly associated protein CsgA, CsgC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CsgA, CsgC genes are directly PCRed from E coli. DH5alpha genome as a whole. There is a scar sequence between CsgA and CsgC coding region that contains a promoter sequence may constitutively transcript CsgC gene. CsgA protein is the major subunit of Curli Fiber. CsgC may regulate CsgG outer membrane assembly of channel protein CsgG and pore activity through modification of C230 in CsgG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shoujie Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR on genomic DNA from E coli. DH5alpha strain. And site-directed mutation by overlap PCR primers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The PstI loci within CsgA sequence has been replaced from CTGCAG to CTGCCG.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1361997
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CsgB, curlin nucleator protein, minor subunit in curli complex
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CsgB is a secretive protein that attached cells' outer membranes. It plays key role in curli fiber polymerization. CsgB is the nucleator for CsgA aggregation in vivo, that facilitate the transformation of soluble CsgA into polymer fiber.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shoujie Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: PCR on genomic DNA from E coli. DH5alpha strain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: CsgB can be designed under inductively control while make CsgACEFG genes constitutively express respectly. Using this method could achieve the immediate synthesis of curli fiber after inducer has been added.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pBAD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pBAD is an E.coli promoter that is induced by L-arabinose. K206000 is a mutagenized pBAD promoter that is responsive to lower concentrations of arabinose than wild type (I13453) and, additionally, exhibits a higher maximum of protein expression as measured by coupling to a fluorescent reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Amelia Hardjasa
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence was obtained by applying all mutations that upregulated AraC binding and subsequent promoter activity listed in reference [1].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special design considerations.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cheZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cheZ, chemotaxis regulator, protein phosphatase for CheY
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Polar localization is dependent on CheA-short. CheZ is a cytosolic phosphatase which functions in the chemotaxis signal transduction complex. Plays an important role in bacterial chemotaxis signal transduction pathway by accelerating the dephosphorylation of phosphorylated CheY (CheY-P).
